ormal encounters, death being reserved for<br>1) being trained<br>2) Over pulls (training your self)<br>3) Raids and epic encounters<br><br>I know that when we where young many fights where dangerous, there was risk involved.<br><br>Let me see in the year 2002 I have died 2 times maybe 3 as an enchanter (non raid). Some of that time includes periods when I play 3 characters at once, this I normaly do in spell drop city so we end up fighting lvl 52 mobs that hit hard.<br><br>Even so, pulling a lvl 52 when I am playing all 3 the odds of dieing are 0% if I am not totaly stupid and if stupid they still only go up to about 4%.<br><br>Maybe my 5000+ hours of play means I have worked out too much of the game BUT it would be nice to have a little more risk of death I recon.<br><br>What is EQ about? Hate management, purely and simply eq is about the hate list. If you control it, you control the game. The only remaining issues are can you do eneough damage / heal eneough for the mob to run out of health before you run out of mana/hp. Thats it :-(<br><br>I dream that they will change the UI so mobs do different things. I would love to see mobs<br><br>1) Randomly attack someone in the group, stick to them and kill them and try and kill them<br><br>2) Randomly hit everyone in the group, maybe stay for a few seconds on one then go for another.<br><br>3) Run away more often, random chance of turning and legging it<br><br>4) Have a chance of deciding to kill people in the group depending on class, kill the wizard first or the cleric or X but some higher scheme<br><br>Basically I should not be able to play 3 characters and grinde with effeciency and safety, there should be risk. Hell thats as a trio, groups of 6 grinde, the risk there should be 0.00000%<br><br>Still I am hopeful that new UI wills be created, I cannot wait to see a cleric mob DA and leg it at half health in to the dungeon.<br><br>Even randomness would be better than the way it is. I can predict 99.99% of what will happen in a single mob encounter. I can decide who gets hit when etc etc. ooh now theres a though<br><br>5. Mob wipes its own hate list randomly<br><br>This would stop us doing the get agro method on tanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>The point is, all of these changes would make it harder BUT with good team work they can all be over come, root control, ping ponging many different tactics could be evolved. BUT when you pull mob X there might actualy be say 5 different tactics you will have to switch between to win. Not just 1 tactic.<br><br>Its kinda why I like fighting in places that get many random adds (glad you did not die Jhary last nite :-) it makes it seem at least more dangerous. Okay so I should not have been an enchanter this time round to really be challenged but damn its fun for a control freak like me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Maybe I am wrong, maybe folks hate the risk of death. Maybe people just want to log on grinde for 10 hours, gain some exp and log. Just another day in the factory called eq.<br><br>I know sometimes I just want to kill things without thinking and get some exp but . . .<br><br>Maybe have safe zones when the mobs AI are dumb and the rest of the world with AI that might actually stop us sleeping . . .<br><br>Hugs to all<br><br>Intra lvl 55 enchantress<br>Sena lvl 55 monket <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 480<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/7/02 3:41:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAdd